==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stupendous
<hw>Stu*pen"dous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stupendus</ets> astonishing, p. future pass. of <ets>stupere</ets>
to be astonished at. Cf. <er>Stupid</er>.]</ety> <def>Astonishing;
wonderful; amazing; especially, astonishing in magnitude or elevation;
<as>as, a <ex>stupendous</ex> pile</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>stupendous</xex> sum.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All are but parts of one <qex>stupendous</qex> whole.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Stu*pen"dous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Stu*pen"dous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stupeous</ent>⟦br⟧
